OL,6,FAt the hearing, the judge ssaid Joyner
OL,7,Fhad intended to kill the woman ` and
OL,8,Fhe thought he had killed her.
OL,10,FIn a statement which was read out in
OL,11,Fcourt on her behalf, the victim said:
OL,12,F"This incident has changed my life.
OL,14,F"I do not know or understand why this
OL,15,Fhas happened to me. I am now very
OL,16,Ffearful of men and will never trust a
OL,17,Fman again.
